12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2014 of Title 62, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. For entities obtaining funding pursuant to subsection G of
17 Section 2003 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes and subsections A
18 and B of Section 2007 of Title 62 the Oklahoma Statutes, each entity
19 shall develop a plan to measure the qualitative effects of projects
20 funded through the Rural Economic Action Plan of 1996. The plan may
21 utilize inquiries or surveys of the public, local governments, or
22 municipalities to measure the effects.
23 B. On or before January 1, 2028, each entity required to
24 develop a plan pursuant to subsection A of this section shall submit
